      • getInvalidDataflows

        public Map<TokenProcessingEntity,DataflowValidationReport> getInvalidDataflows()
        Description copied from interface: DataflowValidationReport
        An entity will be marked invalid if it depends on a nested dataflow which itself is invalid. If this is the case the entity will be be present both in DataflowValidationReport.getFailedEntities() and can be used as a key with this method to get the DataflowValidationReport explaining how the nested dataflow failed.
        Specified by:
        getInvalidDataflows in interface DataflowValidationReport

      • getUnresolvedOutputs

        public List<? extends DataflowOutputPort> getUnresolvedOutputs()
        Description copied from interface: DataflowValidationReport
        The workflow will be marked as invalid if any of the dataflow output ports can't be typed based on incoming links. This happens if the port isn't linked (a common enough issue for new users in previous releases of Taverna) or if the internal port is linked but the entity it links to isn't validated.
        Specified by:
        getUnresolvedOutputs in interface DataflowValidationReport
        Returns:
        a list of DataflowOutputPort implementations which are not typed correctly. These will have output depth of -1 indicating an unknown depth, they may or may not have a granular depth set but if the overall depth is -1 this isn't important as the thing won't run anyway.

      • getUnsatisfiedEntities

        public List<? extends TokenProcessingEntity> getUnsatisfiedEntities()
        Description copied from interface: DataflowValidationReport
        The workflow will be marked as invalid if there are entities with unlinked input ports or where there are cycles causing the type checking algorithm to give up. In these cases offending processors or any ancestors that are affected as a knock on effect will be returned in this list.
        Specified by:
        getUnsatisfiedEntities in interface DataflowValidationReport
        Returns:
        list of TokenProcessingEntity instances within the Dataflow for which it is impossible to determine validity due to missing inputs or cyclic dependencies

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Description copied from interface: DataflowValidationReport
        Overall validity - if the workflow is valid it can be run, otherwise there are problems somewhere and a facade can't be created from it.
        Specified by:
        isValid in interface DataflowValidationReport
        Returns:
        whether the workflow is valid (true) or not (false)

      • isWorkflowIncomplete

        public boolean isWorkflowIncomplete()
        Description copied from interface: DataflowValidationReport
        Whether the workflow is incomplete, i.e. contains no processors and no connected output ports. For example, it is empty or contains only input ports. Even though one can technically run such a workflow it should be prohibited as it does not make any sense. If a workflow is incomplete DataflowValidationReport.isValid() should return false.
        Specified by:
        isWorkflowIncomplete in interface DataflowValidationReport
        Returns:
        whether the workflow is incomplete or not
